The Lagos State Ministry of Education has announced new dates for three entrance examinations postponed earlier this month. The examinations conducted by the Lagos State Examinations Board are: Basic Education Certificate Examination (BECE), Placement Test into Lagos State Public Secondary Schools and Screening Test into Lagos State Junior Model Colleges and Upgraded Junior Secondary Schools.Â  They were initially scheduled to hold between June 3 and July 13 but were postponed due to irregular online registration. According to a circular released from the Office of the Director, Lagos State Examinations Board, Dr. Oluwafemi Hassan, BECE will hold July 15-23, 2019; Placement Test, July 27; and Screening Test, July 20.